Basic usage
{"a":42}	['42']
{"b":"Hello"}	['Hello']
{"a":[1,2,3],"c":"2020-01-01"}	['[1,2,3]','2020-01-01']
With max_dynamic_paths=1 (some paths go to shared data)
{"a":42}	['42']
{"b":"Hello"}	['Hello']
{"a":[1,2,3],"c":"2020-01-01"}	['[1,2,3]','2020-01-01']
With max_dynamic_paths=0 (all paths in shared data)
{"a":42}	['42']
{"b":"Hello"}	['Hello']
{"a":[1,2,3],"c":"2020-01-01"}	['[1,2,3]','2020-01-01']
With typed paths
{"a":42,"b":"Hello"}	['42','Hello']
{"a":0,"b":"World"}	['0','World']
Empty JSON
{}	[]
Nested paths
{"a":{"b":1,"c":2},"d":3}	['1','2','3']
Multiple types in same path across rows
{"a":42}	['42']
{"a":[1,2,3],"c":"2020-01-01"}	['[1,2,3]','2020-01-01']
{"b":"Hello"}	['Hello']
